The paper discusses the field of automated image analysis for X-ray cargo imagery, which involves various computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on security-related threats and smuggling, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses material discrimination and segmentation, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of Threat Image Projection (TIP) and Automated Threat Detection (ATD) suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
